###Block: Basic Traits: Combat Traits
# Ability Name	Unique Key				Category of Ability		Type						Multiple Requirements																			Description																																								Save checks bonus				Combat bonus					Misc bonus			Source Page		Description of the Benefits
Excitable		KEY:Excitable ~ Trait		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.CombatTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Excitable ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.CombatTrait]	PRERACE:1,Gnome		BONUS:COMBAT|INITIATIVE|3|TYPE=Trait	DESC:You demand that everything must happen right now, no matter what, and are too impatient to wait for everyone else to catch up. You finish people's sentences, blurt out the punch lines to slowly-told jokes, rarely make plans, and leap headlong into anything that looks like it might get interesting. While this has sometimes gotten you in trouble, it's also trained you to start moving a split second before everyone else, and that's saved your hide a few times as well.		SOURCEPAGE:pg.19
#Rapscallion		KEY:Rapscallion ~ Trait		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.CombatTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Rapscallion ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.CombatTrait]	PRERACE:1,Gnome		BONUS:SKILL|Escape Artist|1|TYPE=Trait	BONUS:COMBAT|INITIATIVE|1|TYPE=Trait	DESC:You've spent your entire life thumbing your nose at the establishment, and you take pride in your run-ins with the law. Somehow, despite all the mischievous behavior in your life, you've never been caught-you always manage to stay one step ahead of your pursuers.		SOURCEPAGE:pg.19
Sprint			KEY:Sprint ~ Trait			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.CombatTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Sprint ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.CombatTrait]	PRERACE:1,Gnome		BONUS:MOVEADD|TYPE.Walk|5|PREVARLT:ENCUMBERANCE,1	DESC:You were taught from a young age that the world is full of big, fast, dangerous foes, and that sometimes the best course of action is to put your head down and run. Your parents taught you how to make the most of a solid mid-length sprint and how to squeeze just a little extra speed out of yourself.	SOURCEPAGE:pg.19

