# Ability Name		Unique Key					Category of Ability		Type						Multiple Requirements																				Description																																																							Stackable?	Multiple?	Choose														Caster level										Bonus to skill										Class Skill			Source Page		Description of the Benefits																																																																											Bonus
Charlatan		KEY:Charlatan ~ Trait		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.MagicTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Charlatan ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.MagicTrait]	PRERACE:1,Gnome		 PREALIGN:NG,TN,NE,CG,CN,CE		 DESC:Your talent for illusion goes beyond a mere knack for figments and phantasms. You can actually channel spell energy into simple illusions that augment your attempts at deception. As a swift action, you may expend one prepared spell or spell slot to gain a bonus on the next Bluff check you make, provided the check takes place before the beginning of your next turn. The bonus on this check is equal to the level of the spell consumed. You may use this ability 3 times per day.	SOURCEPAGE:pg.19
Naturally Gifted		KEY:Naturally Gifted ~ Trait		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.MagicTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Narurally Gifted ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.MagicTrait]	PRERACE:1,Gnome		DESC:For unknown reasons, you have deeper reserves of magical energy than those around you. Perhaps you are descended from a family of powerful arcane casters, or maybe you believe this trait marks you as destined for magical greatness. Wherever the truth lies, you gain an additional use of one of your gnome magic spell-like abilities each day. This does not always have to be the same spell-like ability-one day you might use dancing lights twice, only to use the additional casting for speak with animals the next day.	 SOURCEPAGE:pg.20
Trickster			KEY:Trickster ~ Trait			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.MagicTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trickster ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.MagicTrait]	PRERACE:1,Gnome		BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|SUBSCHOOL.Illusion|1|TYPE=Trait	DESC:You are particularly adept with your racial spell-like abilities, and as child you quickly learned how dancing lights and ghost sound could be used to amuse your friends and fool your elders. This natural talent for illusion continued as you grew older, and before long you were being offered training in more advanced figments and glamers. You gain a +1 trait bonus to your caster level when determining the duration, range, and area of all spells from the illusion school.	SOURCEPAGE:pg.20

###Block: Basic Traits: Faith Traits
# Ability Name			Unique Key						Category of Ability		Type						Multiple Requirements																					Description																																															Stackable?	Multiple?	Choose											Save checks bonus				Bonus to skill										Modify VAR																																																									Class Skill		Source Page		Description of the Benefits
First Memories		KEY:First Memories ~ Trait		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.FaithTrait.GnomeMagic	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,First Memories ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.FaithTrait]	PRERACE:1,Gnome		DESC:For your whole life, you've felt there was a world just beyond the fabric of the material objects around you, and sometimes you can hear the north wind calling you or smell the dread taint of polluted water before you taste it. You do not gain the normal list of spell-like abilities for the gnome magic racial trait presented in the Pathfinder RPG Core Rulebook. Instead, if you have a Wisdom of 11 of higher, you gain the following spell-like abilities: 1/day—detect poison, know direction, stabilize, and speak with animals. The caster level for these effects is equal to your character level. The DC for these spells is equal to 10 + the spell's level + your Wisdom modifier.	SOURCEPAGE:pg.20
Zealot			KEY:Zealot ~ Trait					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.FaithTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Zealot ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.FaithTrait]	PRERACE:1,Gnome		PRETEXT:You must match the alignment of your chosen deity exactly.	CSKILL:Knowledge (Religion)		BONUS:SKILL|Knowledge (Religion)|1|TYPE=Trait	DESC:You aren't just faithful to the worship of your patron deity-you are obsessively loyal to all of the faith's tenets and guidelines. Your devotion is an anchor that keeps you from drifting away into the throes of the Bleaching, and you cling to it like the life raft it is. As long as you remain completely faithful to the tenets of your faith (as determined by the GM), you never suffer from the Bleaching.	 SOURCEPAGE:pg.20

