# Ability Name						Unique Key					Category of Ability		Type						Multiple Requirements																				Description																																										Multiple?	Choose										Bonus to Ability Pool																																																																																																																							Bonus to skill					Modify VAR						Class Skill			Apply Kit			Source Page		Description of the Benefits
Brastlewark Businessman		KEY:Brastewark Businessman ~ Trait		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.SocialTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Brastlewark Businessman ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.SocialTrait]	PRERACE:1,Gnome		BONUS:SKILL|Craft (Alchemy)|2	DESC:Your time among the gnome elite of Brastlewark in Cheliax has led to an extensive knowledge of alchemy and ready connections in the business.	SOURCEPAGE:pg.20
Collector			KEY:Collector ~ Trait			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.SocialTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Collector ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.SocialTrait]	PRERACE:1,Gnome		MULT:YES	CHOOSE:SKILL|TYPE=Craft|Disable Device|Escape Artist|TYPE=Perform|Spellcraft		DESC:You have a small, bizarre collection of apparently worthless items, such as rusty nails, animal droppings, clockwork cogs, or bent spoons. You find this strange menagerie useful in ways no non-gnome could understand. Seeking new items to add to this collection is endlessly fascinating to you, and while no one else may understand why a Chelish horsenail is worthy to add to your collection when a dwarven wheelbarrow nail is not, it all makes sense to you. Whenever you have your collection within 5 feet of you, you gain a +2 trait bonus on all %1 checks.|%LIST	SOURCEPAGE:pg.20
Explorer			KEY:Explorer ~ Trait		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.SocialTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Explorer ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.SocialTrait]	PRERACE:1,Gnome		DESC:Though many gnomes settle down in communities large enough and interesting enough to provide them with all the stimulation they need to ward off the Bleaching, you’re never going to be one of them. You are always looking around the next bend in the road or over the next hill, past the borders of where you are to where you want to be. At the beginning of each character level, select one desired terrain type from the following list: cold, desert, forest, jungle, mountains (including hills), plains, planes (other than the Material Plane), swamp, underground (including caves and dungeons), urban, or water. You gain a +2 bonus on all Survival checks made in your desired terrain type. At the beginning of each level, you must select a new desired terrain type to replace the old one (you cannot take the same desired terrain type two levels in a row).	SOURCEPAGE:pg.20
Etymologist			KEY:Etymologist ~ Trait			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.SocialTrait	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Etymologist ~ Trait],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.SocialTrait]	PRERACE:1,Gnome		CSKILL:Linguistics		BONUS:SKILL|Linguistics|1|TYPE=Trait	BONUS:LANGUAGES|NUMBER|1	DESC:When you, like all other young gnomes, were taught the hodgepodge Gnome language, you became curious about the original meaning of each word and what language it was derived from. Anytime you come across a new language, you are immediately absorbed by both how it works and what words you can co-opt from it for the Gnome language. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Linguistics checks, know one additional bonus language, and treat Linguistics as a class skill.		SOURCEPAGE:pg.20

